data.text:
AS A SOPHOMORE IN 2019-20

Fall 2019: Stroked the Open 8+ that finished 10th (17:01.03) at the Head of the Riverfront Regatta (10/6) ... Also rowed in the C boat competing in the Collegiate 8+ at Head of the Housatonic (10/12), finishing 25th with a time of 16:23.9.

AS A FRESHMAN IN 2018-19

Spring 2019: Reached the Varsity Eight Grand Final at the Atlantic 10 Championship (5/18), finishing fifth (6:54.115) ... Won the Petite Final (6:29.222) in the Varsity Eight at the Dad Vail Regatta (5/11), nipping conference rival Fordham in a race that came down to the wire ... Won the Quad at the Knecht Cup (4/14), finishing with a time of 7:27.76 which was over 10 seconds faster than second place Harvard ... Also at the Knecht Cup, reached the 2V8 Grand Final and clocked in fourth (7:06.17) ... Had a fourth place finish (7:04.91) in the 2V8 Petite Final at the Doc Hosea Regatta (3/30) ... Won the 2V8 final (7:06.27) at the Cooper Sprints (3/24).

Fall 2018: Tabbed 16th in the Club Eights (17:40.789) at the Head of the Charles (10/20) ... Fifth in the Varsity Eight (16:16.2) at the UMass-hosted Hadley Chase Regatta (10/13) ... Also took seventh (19:52.8) in the Pairs at the Hadley Chase ... Finished fifth in the Pair A Final (8:24.90) at the Small Boat Challenge (10/7)

Carter on UMass: "I chose UMass because of the feeling I got when I first went on the campus. Immediately seeing how large it was I felt like it would offer me everything I wanted in a collegeâ€“new people, new opportunities, and unique places to explore. What really sealed the deal for choosing UMass was the team and girls I met. Even though they barely knew me when I first met them, they still acted as if I were their teammate and friend which made me realize that this is where I fit in."

Before UMass: During her junior year, placed second in the Women's Junior 4x at both the respective MPSRA and New Hampshire state championships ... Won the Women's Junior 4x as a sophomore at the MPSRA State Championships ... Was named Team MVP following her junior campaign and will captain both her high school and club teams in the spring ... Had a 2K personal-best time of 7:36.6 as a junior.

Personal: Daughter of Richard and Roxann Carter ... Has three siblings, Braeden, Mason and Shae ... Was born in Lawrence, Massachusetts ... Enjoys following Red Sox second baseman Dustin Pedroia because he never settles ... Intends to study public health.
